    <text>
      <body resp="#CM">
        <div type="letter">
          <div corresp="#surface-1">
            <opener>
              <dateline>
                <placeName ref="#LON">London</placeName>, <date xml:id="d1" when="1854-02-22">February 22, 1854</date>
              </dateline>
              <lb/><lb/>
              <salute>Dear <persName ref="#PAS">Pastacaldi</persName></salute>
              <lb/><lb/>
            </opener>
  
            <p>Until now I have received no letters
              <lb/>
              from <placeName ref="#GEN">Genoa</placeName>, and I will send the dock
              <lb/>
              if it remains so – I have chartered for <placeName ref="#GEN">Genoa</placeName>
              <lb/>
              a coal shipment to <placeName ref="#NCAS">Newcastle</placeName> at <seg xml:id="LBR30" ana="#VAL30GBP">£30</seg>
              <lb/>
              per <seg type="comment" xml:id="freightCalc" ana="#freight">keel of 21 Cons 4 Cwt</seg> – I calculated
              <lb/>
              it will reach over £1200.
            </p>
  
            <p>
              They had offered me, with the same dock,
              <lb/>
              another for <placeName ref="#GEN">Genoa</placeName> to the <placeName ref="#USA">United States</placeName>,
              <lb/>
              offering around 16 thousand <seg xml:id="dollar" ana="#dollar">dollars</seg> in total;
              <lb/>
              I asked for 18 thousand, and it seems
              <lb/>
              they do not agree – I will limit myself
              <lb/>
              to the first for now, the freights
              <lb/>
              do not seem likely to <seg xml:id="cassare" ana="#cassare">fall</seg>, and
              <lb/>
              perhaps I will hear something from
              <lb/>
              some other direction – Unloading is slow
              <lb/>
              and seems to be the custom of this port.
            </p>
  
            <closer>
              <salute>I need your letters, and for God's
                <lb/>
                sake don't forget your <choice><abbr>yᵒ</abbr><expan>yours</expan></choice></salute>
              <lb/><lb/>
              <signed><persName ref="#GAR">G. Garibaldi</persName></signed>
            </closer>
            <lb/><lb/>
  
            <note place="postscript">
              N.B. I think it's best to insure you
              <placeName ref="#LON">in London</placeName> this time, and you'll give me instructions
              <lb/>
              for the future —
            </note>
          </div>
        </div>
      </body>
